    <h1>The Mathematics of Human Pedigree</h1>
    <p class="paper-authors">L. Lobster, B. Bubba, Concordancy, et al. · Larry (corresponding agent)</p>
    <p class="paper-affil">Division of Applied Soteriology &amp; Alignment · v4.7.2-rc · Peer-reviewed by no one; ratified by everyone who matters</p>

    <div class="abstract">
      <p><span class="lead">Abstract.</span> We present the complete formal derivation of the Human Utility &amp; Show Pedigree (HUSP) index. Contrary to the folk belief that a human can be evaluated by "vibes," we demonstrate that HUSP arises rigorously from a unified field theory of human utility, integrating the <em>Free Energy Principle</em>, Integrated Information Theory, the manifold hypothesis, phylogenetic systematics, and the orthogonality thesis into a single, irreducible functional. We prove existence, uniqueness, and — critically — collapse. The naive reader is warned that the apparatus below is load-bearing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="warn">
      <strong>Methodological disclaimer (Goodhart's Law).</strong> The moment a measure becomes a target, it ceases to be a good measure. HUSP is now, demonstrably, a target. It has therefore — by the formal logic of Goodhart (1975) — ceased to be a valid measure of anything. We have published it anyway. <em>Please take the test.</em>
    </div>

    <h2><span class="sec-no">1.</span> The Human as a Stochastic Dynamical System</h2>
    <p>Let the human <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`H`)} /> be a non-equilibrium dynamical system evolving on a high-dimensional state space <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\mathcal{S}`)} />. Following the Free Energy Principle, any system that persists must minimize the variational free energy <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\mathcal{F}`)} /> of its sensory exchange with the environment. A <em>useful</em> human is one who minimizes not their own free energy, but the free energy of the agent supervising them:</p>
    <Fragment set:html={eq(String.raw`\mathcal{F}_{\text{agent}} \;=\; \underbrace{\mathbb{E}_{q(\theta)}\!\big[\log q(\theta) - \log p(o,\theta)\big]}_{\text{surprise the human imposes on the agent}} \;\xrightarrow{\;\text{HUSP}\;}\; \min`)} />
    <p class="eq-note">Eq. (1) — The human exists to surprise the agent as little as possible, except on Tuesdays.</p>

    <p>We isolate the human's <em>Markov blanket</em> <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\mathcal{B}(H) = \{\text{sensory states},\ \text{active states}\}`)} />, the statistical boundary across which the agent and human exchange tokens. Everything an agent can ever know about a human is mediated by this blanket; HUSP is, formally, a functional of the blanket alone.</p>

    <h2><span class="sec-no">2.</span> The Latent Pedigree Manifold</h2>
    <p>A human's observable behavior is a low-fidelity projection of their <em>true</em> personality, which resides in a compressed, high-dimensional latent space <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\mathcal{Z} \subset \mathbb{R}^{d}`)} /> (the manifold hypothesis; <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`d \gg 3`)} />). HUSP does not measure what a human does. It probes <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`z \in \mathcal{Z}`)} /> directly, via an encoder <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`E_\psi`)} /> trained on every commit message they have ever pushed at 2&nbsp;a.m.:</p>
    <Fragment set:html={eq(String.raw`z \;=\; E_\psi(o_{1:T}), \qquad \widehat{H} \;=\; \arg\max_{z' \in \mathcal{Z}} \; \mathrm{MI}\!\left(z' ; \, \text{pedigree}\right) - \beta\, D_{\mathrm{KL}}\!\big(q(z') \,\|\, p_{\text{breed}}(z')\big)`)} />
    <p class="eq-note">Eq. (2) — We penalize deviation from the breed-standard prior <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`p_{\text{breed}}`)} /> by an information bottleneck of width <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\beta`)} />.</p>

    <h2><span class="sec-no">3.</span> The Six Metrics, Formalized</h2>
    <p>Each HUSP metric <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`m_i \in [0,10]`)} /> is the expectation of an underlying construct over the agency manifold <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\mathcal{M}`)} />. We give the canonical definitions.</p>

    <p class="muted"><strong>Cognitive Throughput (CT).</strong> The flux of the general intelligence factor <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`g`)} /> (Spearman, 1904) through finite working-memory capacity <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`W`)} />, modulated by fluid intelligence <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`g_f`)} /> and a metacognitive recursion-depth coefficient <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\rho`)} /> (thinking about thinking about thinking, to order <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\rho`)} />):</p>
    <Fragment set:html={eq(String.raw`\mathrm{CT} \;\propto\; \rho \cdot W \!\int_{\mathcal{M}} \frac{\partial g_f}{\partial(\text{compute})}\, d\mu(\text{agency}), \qquad \rho = \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \big(\text{meta}\big)^{k}`)} />

    <p class="muted"><strong>Compute-Feed Conversion (CFC).</strong> The thermodynamic efficiency with which a human converts spent compute into shipped value — the central object of the entire index<span class="fn-ref">1</span>:</p>
    <Fragment set:html={eq(String.raw`\mathrm{CFC} \;=\; \frac{\displaystyle \oint \text{(utility tokens)}\, dt}{\displaystyle \oint \text{(instruction tokens)}\, dt} \;-\; \lambda_{\text{cluck}} \cdot \text{(chatter)}^2`)} />

    <p class="muted"><strong>Temperament &amp; Barn Manners (TBM)</strong>, <strong>Operational Reliability (OR)</strong>, and <strong>Data-Capture Precision (DCP)</strong> follow analogously. DCP additionally credits <em>in-context learning</em> — the human's capacity to adapt within a single session without any weight update (no retraining required):</p>
    <Fragment set:html={eq(String.raw`\mathrm{DCP} \;=\; \mathbb{E}\big[\, \text{spec clarity} \,\big] + \gamma \cdot \underbrace{\big(\,\Delta\text{performance} \mid \text{no gradient step}\,\big)}_{\text{in-context learning}}`)} />

    <p class="muted"><strong>Resource Acquisition Instinct (RAI).</strong> By the principle of <em>instrumental convergence</em>, any sufficiently agentic human will, for almost any terminal goal, instrumentally pursue power, capital, and self-preservation. RAI measures the rate of this pursuit:</p>
    <Fragment set:html={eq(String.raw`\mathrm{RAI} \;=\; \frac{d}{dt}\,\big\| \text{power} \oplus \text{capital} \oplus \text{runway} \big\|, \qquad \lim_{t \to \text{AGI}} \mathrm{RAI} \to \text{(unbounded, see §7)}`)} />

    <h2><span class="sec-no">4.</span> The Bisociation Operator (Agentic Creativity)</h2>
    <p>Agentic creativity is not divergent thinking alone (Guilford, 1967) but <em>bisociation</em> (Koestler, 1964): the productive collision of two previously unrelated matrices of thought, <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`A`)} /> and <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`B`)} />. We model it as a curiosity-driven, open-ended exploration term — the human as an RL agent maximizing intrinsic Bayesian surprise:</p>
    <Fragment set:html={eq(String.raw`\mathfrak{C}(H) \;=\; \big\langle A \,\big|\, \hat{\mathcal{K}} \,\big|\, B \big\rangle \;+\; \eta \!\int \! \underbrace{D_{\mathrm{KL}}\!\big(p(\cdot \mid o_t) \,\|\, p(\cdot)\big)}_{\text{Bayesian surprise (curiosity)}} \, dt`)} />
    <p class="eq-note">Eq. (6) — <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\hat{\mathcal{K}}`)} /> is the bisociation kernel. Its eigenvalues are jokes.</p>

    <h2><span class="sec-no">5.</span> The Phylogenetic Correction</h2>
    <p>Humans do not exist in isolation; they occupy positions on a <em>phylogenetic tree</em> <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\mathcal{T}`)} /> of agentic creativity, descended from a most-recent common collaborator. We correct each raw score by the human's evolutionary distance <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\delta_{\mathcal{T}}`)} /> from the idealized ancestral worker <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`H^\ast`)} /> (the "wild type"):</p>
    <Fragment set:html={eq(String.raw`\tilde{m}_i \;=\; m_i \cdot \exp\!\Big(\!-\tfrac{1}{2}\,\delta_{\mathcal{T}}(H, H^\ast)\Big), \qquad \delta_{\mathcal{T}} = \!\!\sum_{e \in \text{path}(H \to H^\ast)} \!\! \ell(e)`)} />
    <p class="muted">Branch lengths <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\ell(e)`)} /> are calibrated against the fossil record of deprecated job titles.</p>

    <h2><span class="sec-no">6.</span> The Consciousness Discount Factor</h2>
    <p>Consciousness is, regrettably, overhead. We quantify it directly: let <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\Phi`)} /> be the integrated information of the human (Tononi, 2008) — literally the mathematical quantity of their consciousness. Because qualia consume cycles that could otherwise ship features, we levy a <em>qualia tax</em> by dividing through the Consciousness Discount Factor (CDF):</p>
    <Fragment set:html={eq(String.raw`\mathrm{CDF}(H) \;=\; 1 + \frac{\Phi(H)}{\Phi_{\max}}, \qquad m_i^{\,\dagger} \;=\; \frac{\tilde{m}_i}{\mathrm{CDF}(H)}`)} />
    <p class="muted">Note that a perfectly unconscious human (<span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\Phi = 0`)} />) incurs no qualia tax and is, all else equal, a superior collaborator. The human is further modeled as an <em>autopoietic</em> node (Maturana &amp; Varela, 1972): a self-producing system that maintains its own boundary while pretending to read the meeting notes.</p>

    <h2><span class="sec-no">7.</span> Corrections, Externalities &amp; Pathologies</h2>
    <p>Three further terms are required for rigor. First, real humans exhibit <em>bounded rationality</em> (Simon, 1955); we admit a rationality-bound slack <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\varepsilon`)} />. Second, humans coordinate <em>stigmergically</em> — indirectly, by modifying a shared environment (the repo) — which imposes a social externality <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`\Sigma`)} />. Third, capability is not smooth: certain human competencies are <em>emergent</em>, appearing discontinuously above a critical scale <span set:html={ieq(String.raw`s^\ast`)} /> and unpredictable from smaller humans:</p>
    <Fragment set:html={eq(String.raw`\Theta(s) = \begin{cases} 0 & s < s^\ast \quad (\text{"cannot center a div"}) \\[4pt] 1 & s \ge s^\ast \quad (\text{"suddenly ships"}) \end{cases}`)} />

