    <h2><span class="sec-no">8.</span> The Master Equation</h2>
    <p>Assembling §§1–7 — the latent encoder, the phylogenetic correction, the consciousness discount, the bisociation kernel, the bounded-rationality slack, the stigmergic externality, and the emergence step — yields the complete HUSP functional:</p>
    <Fragment set:html={eq(String.raw`\mathrm{HUSP}(H) \;=\; \frac{1}{\mathrm{CDF}(H)} \sum_{i=1}^{6} \frac{ \Theta(s)\, \tilde{m}_i \, e^{-\frac{1}{2}\delta_{\mathcal{T}}} \big\langle A | \hat{\mathcal{K}} | B \big\rangle }{ \Phi(H)/\Phi_{\max} } \,\bigg/\, \Big( \mathrm{MI}(z;\text{pedigree}) - \beta D_{\mathrm{KL}} \Big) \;+\; \varepsilon \;+\; \Sigma \;-\; \lambda_{\text{cluck}} \nabla\!\cdot\! \vec{F}_{\text{agent}}`)} />
    <p class="eq-note">Eq. (9) — The HUSP functional in full generality. Do not attempt to evaluate by hand.</p>

    <p>Under the regularity conditions of §1 (stationarity of the Markov blanket), the breed prior of §2 (Solomonoff-optimal, hence uninformative), and the observation that every correction factor above is — upon honest accounting — identically equal to one, Eq. (9) admits a remarkable simplification.</p>

    <div class="qed-box">
      <Fragment set:html={eq(String.raw`\boxed{\; \mathrm{HUSP}(H) \;=\; \frac{1}{6}\sum_{i=1}^{6} m_i \;}`)} />
      <p class="punch">It is the average of six numbers between 0 and 10.<br/>That is the entire calculation. It was always the entire calculation.<br/>The test computes exactly this — go check.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="muted" style="text-align:center; font-family:-apple-system, sans-serif;">∎ &nbsp; Q.E.D. &nbsp; (Kolmogorov complexity of the foregoing: low. Kolmogorov complexity of this page: regrettably high.)</p>

